## Stack
- Python 3.11+
- Anthropic SDK (AsyncAnthropic — always async)
- Textual for TUI
- asyncio.gather for parallel tool calls
- python-docx for export

## Code rules
- Always use AsyncAnthropic, never the sync client
- Tool calls always fire in parallel via asyncio.gather — never sequential
- Every tool function must return a plain string — Claude reads it directly
- Tools never raise exceptions — catch all errors and return an error string
- agent.py and prompts.py are the core product — change these carefully
- definitions.py tool descriptions must include what the tool does NOT find

## File structure
- agent/ — LLM logic only
- tools/ — one file per tool, plus definitions.py
- ui/ — Textual screens only, no business logic
- exports/ — file writers only
- utils/ — csv_validator.py only for now
- tests/fixtures/ — all mock data and sample CSVs live here

## Build order — respect this
Phase 1 (agent core) must work before any other phase is touched.
Do not build TUI or export until commentary output is good.

## Naming
Project is called DeltAgent. Agent function is run_agent(). Tools are search_slack, search_gmail, search_calendar, search_crm.

## Do not
- Add LangGraph or any orchestration framework
- Add synchronous Anthropic API calls
- Add new tools without a definitions.py entry
- Hardcode currency symbols — use a currency variable
- Store secrets anywhere except .env
